Pay Rate: 54.0-55.0 $/Hour
Position Title: Staff Full Stack Developer
Location: Chicago IL
Duration: Contract To Hire Position - 6 Months Plus

Job Description:
The growth and evolution of the power Transmission & Distribution (T&D) industry combined with the rapidly changing technological landscape presents significant opportunities to those companies that have the focus and foresight to take advantage of them. One area of focus for Burns & McDonnell (BMcD) is equipping our clients and workforce with superior data-driven decision-making capability. To that end, we have identified the need to establish a technology position focused on full stack software development.

The Full Stack Developer will be tasked with executing projects and leading engineering teams to tackle key data-driven technology initiatives. This position will report to the BMcD T&D Chicago Innovation and Development Manager and will work collaboratively with the national BMcD Innovation & Development team.
We are looking for a highly skilled computer programmer who is comfortable with both front and back-end programming. Responsibilities include participating in user interviews, developing, and designing front end web user interfaces from a composable architecture, integrating existing data sets and models, developing and maintaining semantically driven object ontologies, and ensuring the responsiveness of applications, among other duties.
This position will be required to see out a project from conception to final product, requiring excellent organizational skills and attention to detail.

JOB DUTIES
• Participation in user interviews to understand technical and customer needs.
• Developing front end website architecture based on Palantir Foundry.
• Designing user interactions on web pages within Palantir Foundry Workshop.
• Developing back-end website code logic that leverages semantic object linking (ontologies) within Palantir Foundry Code Workbook and Ontology Manager.
• Creating servers, databases, and datasets for functionality as needed.
• Ensuring health of data connections and pipelines (utilizing filesystem, JDBC, SFTP, and webhook).
• Ensuring conformance with security protocols and markings on sensitive data sets.
• Ensuring responsiveness of web applications developed on low code/no code solutions.
• Ensuring cross-platform optimization for mobile phones.
• Seeing through projects from conception to finished product.
• Meeting both technical and customer needs.
• Staying abreast of developments in web applications and programming languages.
• Lead other engineers to develop features on your projects.

Requirements:• Degree in computer science preferred or equivalent experience required (3-5 relevant experience).
• Strong organizational and project management skills.
• Proficiency with low-code/no-code tools, Palantir Foundry experience preferred.
• Proficiency with fundamental front-end languages such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
• Familiarity with JavaScript libraries such as Lodash, Math.js, Moment, Numeral, and es6-shim.
• Proficiency with server-side languages for structured data processing; Python, PySpark, Java, Apache Spark, and SparkSQL in particular.
• Familiarity with database technology such as MySQL, Oracle, MongoDB, and others.
• Familiarity with analytical tools for business intelligence and data science such as Power BI, Jupyter, and R Studio.
• Excellent verbal communication skills.
• Excellent problem-solving skills.
• Attention to detail.
• Team leadership experience preferred.

Signal and Image Processing Engineer - Sonar
3 year contract
Lexington MA
Active Secret Clearance REQUIRED

Group Description:
The BMDS Integration Group supports the Missile Defense Agency in the development, deployment, testing, and enhancement of the Ballistic Missile Defense System. This Group performs detailed system and component engineering, flight and ground test analysis, and advanced capability development in collaboration with the contractors and government program offices that are building the missile defense elements and components.
Summary of Position:
Researches, designs, develops and verifies signal and image collection systems, and defines and develops processing and dissemination computer algorithms. Develops requirements analysis, system architecture, and integrates new signal and image capture and processing technology systems. Designs, develops and analyzes systems for the extraction of information from sensors. Systems utilization includes implementation of signal and image processing with advanced computer architectures.
The Group is need of a Signal and Image Processing Engineer to support the analysis of radar data in order to understand the real world ballistic missile threat as well as to evaluate missile defense system performance following flight tests.
Responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Analyze metric and signature radar data from a wide variety of high-power, high resolution radar Sensors perform data processing and analysis as well as prepare data deliverables for missions conducted in support of the Missile Defense System (MDS) development
Author mission summary reports and evaluate sensor performance; regularly contribute material to sponsor briefings and conference papers.
The ideal candidate will ensure that the data is exploited for maximum impact for the continuing development of the MDS.
Required Skills
Significant experience in MATLAB is required 5 plus years and at least 2+ year(s) of experience using MATLAB for data analysis
Experience with Linux operating systems
Candidates should be well versed in standard signal processing techniques (Fourier transforms, filters, etc).
Ability to work well independently as well as with a team
Must possess excellent communication skills
Desired Skills
Experience or background in RF analysis of ballistic missiles is highly desired

Design and develop programming systems, making specific determinations about system design and performance.

Analyze, design, coordinate and supervise the development of software systems to form a basis for the solution of information processing problems.

3 year contract
Lexington MA
Active Secret Clearance REQUIRED

Group Description:
The BMDS Integration Group supports the Missile Defense Agency in the development, deployment, testing, and enhancement of the Ballistic Missile Defense System. This Group performs detailed system and component engineering, flight and ground test analysis, and advanced capability development in collaboration with the contractors and government program offices that are building the missile defense elements and components.
Summary of Position:
Researches, designs, develops and verifies signal and image collection systems, and defines and develops processing and dissemination computer algorithms. Develops requirements analysis, system architecture, and integrates new signal and image capture and processing technology systems. Designs, develops and analyzes systems for the extraction of information from sensors. Systems utilization includes implementation of signal and image processing with advanced computer architectures.
The Group is need of a Signal and Image Processing Engineer to support the analysis of radar data in order to understand the real world ballistic missile threat as well as to evaluate missile defense system performance following flight tests.
Responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Analyze metric and signature radar data from a wide variety of high-power, high resolution radar Sensors perform data processing and analysis as well as prepare data deliverables for missions conducted in support of the Missile Defense System (MDS) development
Author mission summary reports and evaluate sensor performance; regularly contribute material to sponsor briefings and conference papers.
The ideal candidate will ensure that the data is exploited for maximum impact for the continuing development of the MDS.
Required Skills
Significant experience in MATLAB is required 5 plus years and at least 2+ year(s) of experience using MATLAB for data analysis
Experience with Linux operating systems
Candidates should be well versed in standard signal processing techniques (Fourier transforms, filters, etc).
Ability to work well independently as well as with a team
Must possess excellent communication skills
Desired Skills
Experience or background in RF analysis of ballistic missiles is highly desired

Job Title:    Sr. Software Engineer - National Weather Service Office of Water Prediction - Remote

Location:    Silver Spring, MD  & Tuscaloosa, AL - Remote 
Clearance:  Must be able to obtain a Public Trust clearance
 Description:
IBSS is seeking to fill a position to provide Software Engineer support to the National Weather Service (NWS) Office of Water Prediction. The candidate shall support the Atlas 15 program with the creation of precipitation extremes data taking into account a changing climate.
 Key Responsibilities:
In coordination with the team, develop and expand software used in the creation of a repository of observed historical precipitation gauge data, covering CONUS and OCONUS, that will be used to develop estimates for NOAA Atlas 15 Volume 1.  The national precipitation repository shall contain both the full precipitation gauge time series and the derived extreme event time series. The repository shall be developed in line with the FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, and Reusable) principles to facilitate stewardship and future national updates. 
Implement automatic quality control practices, including machine learning evaluation techniques, based on best practices, and the extraction of the extreme time series data based on current Atlas 14 protocols
Work with the Project Investigators (PIs) from NOAA and academia to validate and improved software  developed for the Atlas 15 framework.
Organize and maintain technical documents and data libraries utilizing electronic records management best practices.
Assist scientists with the creation of deliverable and ad-hoc software
 Required Skills /Education/ Certifications & Qualifications: 
Masters or Bachelors of Science degree in computer science, engineering, or IT related field.
8-10 years software engineering/development
Knowledge of statistical analysis and computing, machine learning, processing large data sets, data visualization, and big data programming


Desired Skills:
Experience with climate model and climate data would be a strong plus.
Experience with Google suite products and tools. 

 About IBSS Corp.
IBSS is a Woman-Owned business. Since 1992, IBSS has provided specialized professional, scientific, technical, cybersecurity, IT, and software engineering solutions to the Federal sector. Our clients include the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), the Department of Defense (DoD), and the Department of Justice (DOJ).
